The paper deals with the equivalence between state transformer semantics and predicate transformer semantics in a domain theoretical setting for programs combining nondeterminism and probability. This involves concepts from logic (such as predicate transformers), programming languages (such as state transformers), information theory (such as entropicity), and data structures (such as discrete state spaces). Therefore, likely arXiv CS sub-categories include cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
